section: The duration of this Venture (the "Term") will begin on March 1, 2020 and continue in full force and effect until February 28, 2025, unless terminated earlier by mutual agreement of the Managers.
explanation: The Term section defines the duration of the joint venture as starting on March 1, 2020, and ending on February 28, 2025. However, the Execution Date is defined as 'this 20th day of Friday, March 2020'. There is a potential conflict arising if the agreement is fully executed *after* the official start date of the joint venture on March 1, 2020.

section: Each of the Members has contributed to the capital of the Venture, in cash or property in agreed upon value, as follows (the "Capital Contribution"): Member Contribution Description Agreed Value BorrowMoney.com, inc 1, 500 square feet of Leased/rent office Space Includingspecified Description of duty* $3,500,000.00 USD JVLS, LLC dba Vaccines 2Go $60,000.00 USD From Monthly Government , City And State, And Or Private Awarded Contracts. Plus (10%) Of Any Generated Gross Revenue, In Add i t i on to The To ta l Contributions. $3,500,000.00 USD
explanation: The agreement assigns a value of $3,500,000.00 USD to both BorrowMoney.com, inc's contribution of office space and JVLS, LLC's contribution of $60,000.00 USD from contracts plus 10% of gross revenue. This raises concerns about whether the assigned values accurately reflect the fair market value of each contribution. It seems highly unlikely that $60,000.00 USD plus 10% could be considered the same as $3,500,000.00 USD. The values are not equal to each other.

section: The exclusive purpose of the Venture (the "Purpose") will be IT Development. internet Back office Maintenance And Deployment of medical Service.
explanation: The term 'internet Back office Maintenance And Deployment of medical Service' is vague, leading to multiple interpretations of what it means. The sentence is not structured properly and does not make sense.
